Conlon is an Irish family name, the gaelic spelling being Ó Connalláin. It is a variartion of the anglcised version of Ó Connalláin. It is sometimes spelt Conlan.
The family motto is Inter Utrumque, meaning between both sides.
There is a small town in Mayo, Ireland called Bonniconlon, with a Conlon's bar.